> Mexican-style rice bowls are always welcome on our table, and this one is an instant winner. You'll sizzle up juicy spiced dark meat chicken and serve it over a bed of fluffy rice. Top with zesty lime crema, and serve alongside mashed black beans sprinkled with crumbled cotija cheese. A squeeze of lime juice just before serving brings it all together.

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, juice from half the lime, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{}, and as much lime zest as you like.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Chicken ==

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and scallion whites; season with half the @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, @water{1%tbsp}, and juice from one lime wedge.

== Black Beans ==

While chicken cooks, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, remaining @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, @butter{1%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until butter has melted and beans are warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Using a #potato masher{} or fork, gently mash half the beans. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice, beans, and chicken between #bowls{} in separate sections. Drizzle chicken with crema; sprinkle @cotija cheese{1/2%cup}(crumbled) over beans. Garnish everything with scallion greens. Squeeze remaining lime wedge over the top and serve.

> Cook poultry until internal temperature reaches 165° for food safety.